Q. Difference between print() and println() ?

-> print() method is used to print the statement and keeps cursor in the same line.
-> println() method is used to print the statement and move the cursor to next line.




==============
Loops in Java
==============

Loops are used to execute statements repeatedly

We have below loops in java
---------------------------

1. while loop
2. do while loop
3. for loop
4. for-each (arrays & collections)



while loop
===========
-> it is going to execute statements until condition is true

syntax:
-------

while(condition){

//stmts
}

ASSIGNMENT:
===========
write a java program to print 1 to 10 using while loop

-------------------------------------------------------


public class Count {

	public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {

		int i = 1;
		
		while(i<=10) {
			
			System.out.println(i);
			i++;
		}
	}

}

