===================
Branching statement
====================

in java, we have 3 branching statements 

1. break
2. continue
3. return


-> break is used to come out from switch case or loop
-> continue is used to skip one iteration in the loop
-> return is used to come out from method execution 


break
=====
Example
-------

public class Count {

	public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {

		for(int i =1 ; i <= 5; i ++){
			
			if(i > 2) {
				break;
			}
			
			System.out.println(i);
		}
	}

}


===================
    continue
===================

Example
=======


public class Count {

	public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {

		for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {

			if (i > 5) {
				continue;
			}

			System.out.println(i);
		}
	}

}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Note: After 5 , condition is true, so the loop is skipped here ..




